Step by Step guide:
- Clone the git repository (main branch):
  git clone https://github.com/fran-felix/jarvis.git

- Configure .env variables:
  MODEL, the chat model name
  CHAT_API_KEY, the chat model api key 
  CHAT_BASE_URL, the url where the model is hosted
The AI model was provided through an API, managed by an university laboratory (LIA - Laboratório de Inteligência Artificial)
  LOCAL_EMBEDDING_MODEL, the embedding model name
  LOCAL_API_KEY, the embedding model api key
  LOCAL_LLM_BASE_URL, the url
These are labelled "LOCAL" because we used a local model to handle embedding creation and maintenance.

- Running the project:
  We also used UV, a python project manager for better handling of our project. Use "uv run basic_ui.py" to start the application.
  If handling the project in another manner, just remember to start the project through "basic_ui.py"!

Tools used:
- Langchain library provided the framework for RAG and AI handling
- Llama and local AI models
- SQLite for application database
- ChromaDB for embedding database
- UV to handle dependencies and set up the project environment

AI tools used:
- GitHub Copilot for most of the code generation and assistent/agent support
- Gemini for debugging and information fetching when our problems were way too specific.
Especially when Copilot's credits were almost over